The '''Late Holocene Rainforest Crisis''' was a loss of [[African rainforest]]s which happened around 600BC, with the [[Rainforest|forests]] being replaced by dryer [[savanna]]. After around 600 years the forests grew back. As causes for the crisis, both [[Climate change|natural climate change]] and human interference have been proposed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/science/2018/02/did-humans-or-climate-cause-the-great-rainforest-crisis/|title=African rainforests vanished for 600 years, then bounced back—why?|publisher=Ars Technica}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Bostoen|first=Koen|last2=Clist|first2=Bernard|last3=Doumenge|first3=Charles|last4=Grollemund|first4=Rebecca|last5=Hombert|first5=Jean-Marie|last6=Muluwa|first6=Joseph Koni|last7=Maley|first7=Jean|date=2015-06-01|title=Middle to Late Holocene Paleoclimatic Change and the Early Bantu Expansion in the Rain Forests of Western Central Africa|url=https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/abs/10.1086/681436|journal=Current Anthropology|volume=56|issue=3|pages=354–384|doi=10.1086/681436|issn=0011-3204}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Maley|first=Jean|last2=Doumenge|first2=Charles|last3=Giresse|first3=Pierre|last4=Mahé|first4=Gil|last5=Philippon|first5=Nathalie|last6=Hubau|first6=Wannes|last7=Lokonda|first7=Michel O.|last8=Tshibamba|first8=John M.|last9=Chepstow-Lusty|first9=Alex|date=2018-01-01|title=Late Holocene forest contraction and fragmentation in central Africa|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/quaternary-research/article/late-holocene-forest-contraction-and-fragmentation-in-central-africa/97E7BBD33C8036A9DB92EE4C0B89905F|journal=Quaternary Research|language=en|volume=89|issue=1|pages=43–59|doi=10.1017/qua.2017.97|issn=0033-5894}}</ref>

