'''N. de Morena''' or '''N. de Morera''', name given to him by his contemporary Fray Juan de Torquemada<ref name="Allen1997">{{cite book|author=John Logan Allen|title=North American Exploration|url=https://books.google.es/books?id=7RGlz9a4wVYC&pg=PA433&dq=torquemada+pilot+morera&hl=ca&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi-hrPDxazOAhXILhoKHTrWBs4Q6AEIGzAA#v=onepage&q=torquemada%20pilot%20morera&f=false|year=1997|publisher=U of Nebraska Press|isbn=0-8032-1015-9|pages=433–}}</ref> and by most authors,<ref name="Polk1991">{{cite book|author=Dora Polk|title=The Island of California: A History of the Myth|url=https://books.google.es/books?id=iKNqcBIbhqMC&pg=PA221&lpg=PA221&dq=drake+pilot+morera&source=bl&ots=7gKbl7QABD&sig=i2_YEZcyfH9dI7wFTWZfYBElIno&hl=ca&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwizjtPKvazOAhUJtBoKHWPFCB4Q6AEIGzAA#v=onepage&q=drake%20pilot%20morera&f=false|publisher=U of Nebraska Press|isbn=0-8032-8741-0|pages=221–}}</ref><ref name="Bawlf2009">{{cite book|author=Samuel Bawlf|title=The Secret Voyage of Sir Francis Drake|url=https://books.google.es/books?id=quFZ3oLYEwoC&pg=PA331&lpg=PA331&dq=drake+pilot+morera&source=bl&ots=UhCheFEgcy&sig=MOejBRyAb-axGGNZp9HkXdDKuMQ&hl=ca&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwizjtPKvazOAhUJtBoKHWPFCB4Q6AEIIDAB#v=onepage&q=drake%20pilot%20morera&f=false|date=1 September 2009|publisher=D&M Publishers Incorporated|isbn=978-1-926706-24-5|pages=331–}}</ref><ref name="Kelsey2000">{{cite book|author=Harry Kelsey|title=Sir Francis Drake: The Queen's Pirate|url=https://books.google.es/books?id=svtPzefAv-MC&pg=PA194&lpg=PA194&dq=drake+pilot+morera&source=bl&ots=ynnIHub8SD&sig=cexqxvFe_E9KrxDi1_ECYh-C0FE&hl=ca&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwizjtPKvazOAhUJtBoKHWPFCB4Q6AEIJTAC#v=onepage&q=drake%20pilot%20morera&f=false|year=2000|publisher=Yale University Press|isbn=978-0-300-08463-4|pages=194–}}</ref><ref name="reform">[http://www.reformation.org/sir-francis-drake.html The Secret Voyage of Sir Francis Drake]</ref> was a European [[Maritime pilot|ship pilot]] who reportedly was left at [[New Albion]] by [[Sir Francis Drake]] in 1579 and then walked to Mexico.  In doing so, he likely was the first European to see [[San Francisco Bay]] and likely established the incorrect idea that [[California]] was an [[Island of California|island]].<ref>{{cite news| journal=The Land of Sunshine, The Magazine of California and the West | title=Narrative of the Pilot Morera, who passed through the North Sea to the South Sea through the Strait | pages=184–186 | URL=http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=hvd.32044099873853;view=1up;seq=204 | issue=February | year=1900 | editor=Charles F. Lumis}}</ref>  In only few and non-contemporaneous references, the name is given as "N. de Morena."<ref>{{cite book | title=REPORT OF FINDINGS RELATING TO THE IDENTIFICATION OF SIR FRANCIS DRAKE'S ENCAMPMENT AT POINT REYES NATIONAL SEASHORE | last=Aker | first=Raymond | year=1970 | URL=http://www.winepi.com/Drake%20Book/Drake-Book-05.pdf | pages=338–340}}</ref>

